description: This walk largely covers the Bondi to Manly Walk aound Sydney Harbour. It is recommended to pick managable sections between public transport hubs across mutiple days.

markers.description: Take the bus to Bondi Beach using transportnsw.info.
From the bus stop at the south end of the beach, enter Notts Ave to the right.
There are public toilets at the steps down to the beach.
From the lookout at Notts Ave, follow the footpath down to the beach.
Follow the promenade along Bondi Beach to the other end.
There are public toilets at the surf club.
From the surf club follow the footpath up to Campbell Parade.
Follow Campbell Parade to the right past the shops.
After the shops, follow Military Road along the golf course.
At the intersection follow Douglas Parade to the right.
At the intersection follow Lola Road to the left.
At the end of Lola Road follow the Raleigh Reserve along the cliffs.
At the sports fields at the other end of the reserve, follow Blake Street to the shops.
At the shops, follow Military Road to the right.
Visit the lookout at Dudley Page Reserve and continue along the footpath.
The barkbench with the best view in Sydney.
markers.title: A Bench with a View
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: At the end of the reserve, follow Lancaster Road to the right.
At the end of Lancaster Road, follow the Waverley Cliff Walk.
At the end of the reserve follow take the steps up to Oceanview Ave.
From the top of the steps follow Ray St to the right.
At the corner of Ray St follow the boardwalk around the apartments.
From Diamond Bay Reserve follow the steps up to Chris Bang Cres
Follow Chris Bang Cres to the right.
After the corner follow Marne St and Jensen Ave straight ahead.
From the corner of Clarke St follow the footpath through Clarke Reserve
Follow the footpath past the sports fields and through Lighthouse Reserve.
At the end of the path, follow Old South Head Rd to the right.
From the corner in Old South Head Rd, follow the path to the right into Gap Park.
Follow the trail through Gap Park along the cliffs.
-3km Optionally from The Gap take the shortcut through Robertson Park to the ferry dock.
There's a toilet block near the playground.
Follow the steps up from The Gap along the cliffs.
At the intersections follow the trail left down to Gap Bluff Rd.
At the bottom of the steps follow Gap Bluff Rd to the right.
At the intersection follow Hornby Light Rd to the left.
Then a the bottom of the zig zag follow Cliff St to the right.
+1kmOptionally follow the sign to the Hornby lighthouse to the right of the beach.
Follow the path that loops around the lighthouse and return back to the beach.
Follow the beach to the left climb the staircase onto the next headland.
Follow the steps up to Pacific St.
Follow the footpath along Pacific St.
Turn right at the intersection with Cove St.
At the corner of Cove St. follow the footpath to the right to Watson Bay Beach.
Follow the path along the beach to the ferry dock.
Take the ferry from/to Watsons Bay using transportnsw.info.
Continue along Marine Pde from the ferry dock.
Follow the footpath along the Yacht Club car park.
Follow the steps up to Palmerson St. from Gibsons Beach.
At the intersection follow Hopetoun Av to the right.
At the 5 way intersection, follow The Crescent.
Enter the park to the right and follow the path down to the Parsley Bay Bridge.
Cross Parsley Bay Bridge and follow the footpath to Fitzwilliam Rd.
After the steps follow Fitzwilliam Rd to the right.
At the corner follow Wentworth Rd to the left.
Follow the path through Vaucluse Park on the right.
At the other side of Vaucluse Park follow Coolong Rd to the right.
At the roundabout follow Greycliffe Ave to the left.
At the corner follow Fig Tree Rd to the Shark Beach Surf Club.
Follow the path from the Surf Club to Steel Point Road.
From the corner in Steele Point Rd follow the signs to the Hermitage Foreshore Walk on the right
Cross Milk Beach and use the steps and continue the Hermitage Foreshore Walk to the right.
Cross Hermit Beach and continue the Hermitage Foreshore Walk to the right.
At the end of the Hermitage Foreshore Walk follow Bayview Hill Rd.
From the intersection follow Tivoli Ave to the right.
From the next intersection follow New South Head Rd to the right to the Rose Bay shops.
From the Rose Bay shops follow the path around Lyne Park on the right.
Follow the footpath around Lyne Park past the Ferry Wharf.
Take the ferry from/to Rose Bay using transportnsw.info.
After the boat ramp follow the esplanade along New South Head Rd to the right.
-2km Alternatively keep following South Head Rd. to cut off a lengthy detour around Point Piper.
At the end of the esplanade follow the footpath right through Rose Bay Park.
From Rose Bay Park follow the steps up to Wunulla Rd.
At the top of the steps follow Wunilla Rd to the right.
Take the steps from Wunulla Rd up to Wyuna Rd.
Follow Wyuna Rd to the right.
Follow the footpath to Lady Martins Beach to the right.
From the intersection follow Wolseley Rd to the left.
Follow Wolseley Rd back to New South Head rd.
From the intersection follow New South Head Rd to the right.
Follow St Mervyns Ave down to Seven Shillings Beach.
Follow seven Shillings Beach to the surf club.
There are public toilets at the surf club.
From the surf club follow the car park back to New South Head Rd.
From the intersection follow New South Head Rd to the right.
From the intersection follow William St to the right.
At the roundabout turn right down Pearce St.
Follow Stafford Rt to the left.
At the end of Stafford St, follow Beach St to the right to Double Bay Beach.
Follow the Double Bay Beach to the ferry wharf.
Take the ferry from/to Double Bay using transportnsw.info.
From the ferry wharf follow the footpath through Steyne Park
There is a public toilet at the far end of Steyne Park.
At end of the park follow Ocean Ave to the left.
At the intersection follow Marathon Mews to the right.
Ascend the steps at the corner of Marathon Mews.
From the top of the steps follow Marathon Rd straight ahead.
-1.5km Optionally, at the end of Marathon Rd follow Darling Point to the left to skip a length detour around Darling Point.
From the end of Marathon Rd follow Darling Point Rd to the right to the Darling Point ferry wharf.
At the intersection follow Thornton St to the left.
Follow the corner in Thornton Rd to the left.
From the intersection turn right and follow New Beach Rd downhill.
At the bottom of the hill follow the footpath through Yarranabbe Park.
Follow the footpath around Rushcutters Bay.
From Rushcutters Bay Park follow the steps up to Holdsworth Rd.
At the intersection follow Elizabeth Bay Rd to the left, then Ithaca Rd to the Marina.
At the Elizabeth Bay Marina, follow Billyard Ave to the left.
Follow the steps up from Billyard Eva to Macleay St.
At the top of the steps cross at the traffic light and follow Challis Ave.
At the end of Challis Ave, follow Victoria St a short distance to the left.
Follow the steps down to Cowper Wharf Roadway.
At the bottom of the steps cross at the traffic lights and make your way left along Cowper Wharf Roadway.
At the start of the wharf the famous Harry's Cafe De Wheels can be found.
Follow the path along the bay along the water.
Take the steps up and follow Mrs Macquaries Rd to the right.
After the Pool follow the footpath along the water.
Follow the footpath around Mrs Macquarie's Chair.
Continue all the way around the waterfront of the Botanical Gardens.
Exit the Botanical Gardens at the Sydney Opera House and follow Circular Quay to the left.
Follow Circular Quay to the ferry wharves and train station.
Take the ferry or train from/to Circular Quay using transportnsw.info.
There are public toilets at the far end of the station.
From First Fleet Park follow the footpath past the museum.
Continue along the shorefront past the Overseas Passengers Terminal.
Follow the footpath around the Hyatt Hotel.
Follow the path through Hickson Road Reserve.
At the other end of the reserve cross the road and follow the steps up to the bridge.
Follow the path along Dawes Point Reserve under the Sydney Harbour Bridge.
Take the steps up to Cumberland St.
Follow Cumberland St to the left.
Use the steps up to the Sydney Harbour Bridge.
Follow the footpath across the Sydney Harbour Bridge.
At the far end of the bridge follow the stairs down into Kirribilli.
Get the train from/to Milsons Point using transportnsw.info.
-3km To skip a long detour around Kirribilli follow Broughton St left from the station.
From the station follow Boughton St to the right to Bradfield Park.
Follow the path through the park to the shorefront.
Follow the footpath to the left along the water.
Take the steps up to Waruda St.
From the top of the steps follow Waruda St to the right.
From the end of Waruda St take the steps up to Kirribilli Ave.
From the top of the stops follow Carabella St straight ahead.
Follow the corner in Carabella St to the left.
At the intersection follow Peel St to the right.
At the intersection follow Elamang Ave to the left.
From the intersection with Willoughby St follow Mc Dougall St straight ahead.
Follow the footpath into Milson Park to the right.
There is a public toilet in the park.
Follow the steps up from the end of Bradley Ave and take the path to the right halfway up the steps.
From the end of the footpath, follow Stannards Pl to the left.
From the intersection follow High St to the right.
At the end of High St follow the footpath left along the shore through Kesterton Park.
There are public toilets at the far end of Kesterton Park.
Follow the shorefront along HMAS Platypus.
From the end of the path follow the steps up to Kiara Cl.
From the gate at the top of the steps follow Kiara Cl.
From the intersection follow Hipwood St to the right.
From the end of Hipwood St follow Clark Rd to the right.
Follow the footpath right through Anderson Park.
There are public toilets at the sports field.
Follow the steps up to Kurraba Rd and follow it to the right.
Use the steps on the right down to Wycombe Rd.
Cross Hayes St and continue following Wycombe Rd.
At the corner follow Wallaringa Av to the right.
At the intersectioon follow Kurraba Rd to the left.
At the next intersection follow Billong St to the right.
At the end of Billong St turn left down Sellcove Rd.
At the intersection follow Honda Rd to the right.
At the next intersection follow Bogota Ave to the right.
From the corner of Bogota Ave follow the footpath into Cremorne Reserve.
Follow the footpath along the waterfront.
At the end of the reserve follow Milsons Rd to the right to the ferry wharf.
Take the ferry from/to Cremorne Point using transportnsw.info.
There is a public toilet up the steps from the ferry wharf.
Follow the path left around the buildings from toilet block.
Take the ferry from/to Old Cremorne using transportnsw.info.
Cross the foot bridge across the gully.
From the rowing club follow the path along Mosman Bay
There is a cafe and toilets at the Mosman Bay ferry wharf.
Take the ferry from/to Mosman Bay using transportnsw.info.
Follow the steps up from the ferry wharf.
At the top of the steps follow Mosman St to the right.
At the intersection follow McLead St uphill to the left.
At the top of the steps follow Musgrave St to the right.
-1km Alternatively take the shortcut between the two apartment buildings straight ahead.
From the ferry wharf follow the steps up to Herron Walk.
At intersection follow Raglan St to the left.
Enter McLeod St on the right.
Follow the steps down from the end of McLeod St.
Follow Curley Camp Rd to Sirius Cove Reserve on the right.
Cross Sirus Cove Park along the beach to the start of the Foreshore Trak.
There's a toilet block at the far side of the park.
Follow the Foreshore Trak right to Curlew Camp.
At the end of the track continue along the footpath to the ferry wharf.
Take the ferry from/to Taronga Zoo using transportnsw.info.
From the ferry wharf follow the footpath to the zoo entrance.
Rarely a zoo is as enjoyable from the outside.
markers.title: You Belong in the Zoo
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: At the zoo entrance, follow Bradleys Head Walking Track to the right.
From the amphitheatre follow the footpath along Bradleys Head Rd past the memorials.
There are public toilets at Bradleys Head.
From the corner in Bradleys Head Rd, follow Taylors Bay Track to the right.
The track ends at Chowder  Bay. Cross the reserve to the wharf on the other side.
There's a toilet block at the picnic area.
Access the wharf and the cafe from end of the beach.
Continue past the cafe and follow the steps on the left up to Chowder Bay Rd.
Cross Chowder Bay Rd and follow the steps to the left of the lodge.
At the top of the steps follow the road a short way to the left and continue the track to Georges Head Lookout.
From the the lookout follow the sign to Manly along Georges Head walking track.
-2.5km Cross the road to skip the detour around Middle Head.
From the crossing follow Middle Head Road to the right.
Follow Middle Head Road to the carpark at Middle Head.
From the carpark follow the walking trail around the gun emplacements.
From the carpark follow Middle Head Rd back past the naval hospital.
From the pedestrian crossing follow the footpath to the right to Balmoral Bay.
A short distance down the footpath take the steps to the right and follow them down to Balmoral Park.
Follow the footpath left or right around Balmoral Park.
From the carpark follow the esplanade along Balmoral Beach past the resaurant.
Take the bus from/to Balmoral Beach using transportnsw.info.
From the end of Belmoral beach follow any of the steps up to Stanton Rd.
At the top of the steps follow Stanton Rd to the right.
At the intersection follow  Burran Ave to the left.
Enter Rosherville Rd on the right and follow the footpath down to the reserve.
From Rosherville Reserve access Chinamans Beach
From the far end of Chinamans Beach follow the steps up to McLean Cres.
From the top of the steps follow McLean Cred to the right uphill.
At the top of the hill take the steps up to Parriwi Rd.
Follow the footpath along Parriwi Rd to the right to the Spit.
There are some cafes and restaurants along the right side of Spit Rd.
Cross Spit Rd at the traffic lights and follow the footpath along Spit Reserve to the right.
There is a public toilet halfway down Spit Reserve.
Take the bus from/to the Spit using transportnsw.info.
From the end of Spit Reserve follow the footpath across the Spit Bridge.
Use the underpass at the other side of the bridge on the left into Ellery's Punt Reserve.
From the reserve follow the Fisher Bay Walk to Sandy Bay.
Follow the footpath along the water around Sandy Bay to Clontarf Reserve.
There is a cafe and a toilet block in Clontarf Reserve.
From the picnic area follow the beach to the end of the reserve.
At high tide follow the detour along Monash Cres to the end of the beach.
From the end Monash Cres enter the beach access.
From the beach follow the steps to the Spit to Manly walk to the left.
At the intersection follow the signs along the Manly Scenic Walkway.
From Castle Rock Beach follow the steps up the Castle Rock Track.
At the intersection with the Lighthouse Track, continue straight. on the Grotto Point Track.
At the Grotto Point Rock Engravings, continue straight on the Grotto Point Track.
At the Dobroyd Headland follow the signs to the Manly Ferry.
There is a toilet block along the trail to the beach.
From Reef Beach follow the signs to Manly along the Reef Beach Track.
Cross the rocks at Forty Baskets Beach to the picnic area along the shore.
Follow the footpath along the picnic area.
There is a toilet block along the trail to the beach.
At the end of the trail follow Gourlay Ave to the left.
After the carpark follow the sign to Manly on the right to Clarence St.
Cross the bridge to Clarence St across the gully.
On the other side of the bridge follow N. Harbour St to the right.
At the corner of N Harbour St take the steps down into North Harbour Reserve.
Follow the footpath along the shorefront to the other side of North Harbour Reserve.
From the other side of the reserve, take the steps up to King Ave.
From the top of the steps follow King Ave to the right.
From the end of King Ave, follow the footpath along Lauderdale Ave to the right.
Follow the N Harbour walk to the right and follow the N Harbour Walk to Fairlight Beach.
From Fairlight Beach follow the Fairlight walk along the shorefront.
There's a toilet block near the rock pool.
At the end of the Fairlight Walk, take the steps down to the aquarium.
From the aquarium follow the esplanade to the ferry wharf.
Plan your return trip from Manly at transportnsw.info.
